This booking is for a Malay family of 2 adults and 4 kids, aged 12, 10, 6 and 5. The family is from Kajang. 

The whole family is into the outdoors, with the husband into motocross, the wife into marathon, the boys into hiking, and the 5-year old baby girl into smiling to people. We'll discuss later with you whether we should take up the option of hiking into the Berembun Forest.

Re: Day Visitor - using pool - Sat Dec 14, 2019 (AJRB-131119)

Hi Izzat,

See below our proposal for your visit. The terms are:
- Visit by 8 adults from Noon until 8pm
- Use of pool and pool towels
- Use of lounge and pool shed area. 
- Use of BBQ facilities
- Dining plates and utensils
- Ice

Does not include:
- BBQ materials
- BBQ chef
- Drinks or any other food items. 

Stuff you can add on:
- BBQ materials. We have a selection of items you can order on our website. Do let us know 
- Excursion options in the morning. Perhaps a challenging hike up Gunung Angsi with a guide or the temuan river trek. Lots of fun. 
- Some of you may decide to stay back a night. I can offer to waive the day costs for those people and give you a 10% room rate discount
- Maybe you may want to try our home brewed Tuak (fermented rice wine) at RM20 a bottle of 750ml
- We also have some famous seremban curry puffs and some cooked meals from our caterer that you can also take a look online. All meals and BBQ items must be preordered. 

Just remember that Awanmulan is a retreat and while we will tolerate a party atmosphere in the afternoons, the evening and night times are meant to be a bit more chilled out and quieter, so loud music in the evenings towards night would not be okay as it will disturb our stay in guests. 

Regards,
Zee
